description:
Your tasks:

- Administer and optimize Microsoft 365 tenant services (Exchange Online, Teams, SharePoint Online, OneDrive, Viva, Copilot);
- Manage device and endpoint configurations using Microsoft Intune across Windows, macOS, iOS, and Android platforms;
- Implement and enforce security, compliance, and governance policies;
- Enhance collaboration, communication, and productivity through integrated Microsoft 365 solutions;
- Provide training, documentation, and knowledge transfer to internal IT staff and end users;
- Assess current Microsoft 365 tenant configuration, policies, and integrations;
- Evaluate existing device management and endpoint security practices;
- Identify gaps in governance, compliance, and automation;
- Engage stakeholders to determine user experience and service improvement needs;
- Administer and configure Microsoft 365 services, including Teams, Exchange, SharePoint, and OneDrive;
- Manage user identities, access control, and licenses through Entra ID and Azure AD;
- Deploy and manage endpoints using Microsoft Intune and Autopilot;
- Implement and maintain security features such as MFA, DLP, Conditional Access, and Defender for Endpoint;
- Oversee device and MFP (Multi-Function Printer) service management;
- Enhance governance models, compliance policies, and reporting frameworks;
- Monitor system performance, user activity, and service health;
- Generate reports on adoption, compliance, security incidents, and usage;
- Provide technical support and serve as escalation point for complex issues;
- Develop and maintain documentation, SOPs, and FAQs for IT staff and users;
- Deliver training and knowledge transfer sessions to strengthen internal Capacity;
- Stay informed on Microsoft roadmap developments and best practices;
- Recommend and implement service and process improvements;
- Assessment and recommendations report on Microsoft 365 and device management;
- Updated configuration and governance documentation;
- Implemented optimization of Microsoft 365 tenant and endpoint environments;
- Support and follow-up on users‚Äô issues and requests;
- Documentation, standard operating procedures (SOPs), and selfhelp resources;
- Final report with recommendations for sustainability and continuous improvement.

Requirements:

- Master‚Äôs degree in IT combined with relevant IT professional experience of 7 years;
- Minimum of 7 years of progressively responsible experience in IT systems administration, cloud platform management, or digital workplace technologies;
- Proven experience managing and optimizing Microsoft 365 environments, including Teams, Exchange Online, SharePoint Online, OneDrive, and Entra ID;
- Extensive experience with endpoint and device management using Microsoft Intune and Autopilot;
- Strong background in IT security, compliance management, and governance frameworks;
- Experience developing or improving IT service delivery models and automation processes;
- Experience with Microsoft 365 administration and governance;
- Experience with Defender for Endpoint;
- Experience with Entra ID (Azure AD) and Conditional Access management;
- Experience with Microsoft Security and Compliance Center configuration;
- Experience with Data governance and reporting within M365;
- Experience with Endpoint configuration, patch management, and security;
- Experience with Automation and PowerShell scripting;
- Knowledge of networking fundamentals and hybrid cloud integration;
- Prior experience with an international organization is a strong asset;
- The following certificates are required: Microsoft Certified Expert in M365 Productivity or Security, Microsoft Certified: Modern Desktop Administrator Expert, Microsoft Certified: Security Operations Analyst Associate or equivalent, ITIL Foundation certification preferred;
- Excellent command of the English.
